    <string-array name="assistant_guide_capabilities">
        <item>Answer learning questions using the configured OpenAI-compatible service and optional local search results.</item>
        <item>Create editable Markdown node drafts from requests like "create a note" or "创建笔记".</item>
        <item>Improve an existing Node, Quiz, or Capture slip while preserving its local identity and revision check.</item>
        <item>Suggest an existing Area for a draft; the user reviews the editor before anything becomes a saved node.</item>
        <item>Run interview-style review: ask one question, evaluate the answer, and save a daily review card.</item>
        <item>Keep same-window conversation context as role messages, with older turns compacted locally when needed.</item>
        <item>Ask for lightweight confirmation or context selection when a generation step needs your decision.</item>
    </string-array>
    <string-array name="assistant_guide_workflow">
        <item>Start with a concrete task: "创建笔记：主题", "improve this node", or "ask me one review question".</item>
        <item>Use the generated draft as a proposal, then open the editable draft and save only after checking the content and Area.</item>
        <item>Prefer focused follow-ups in the same assistant window; the app now sends prior user and assistant turns as conversation messages.</item>
        <item>If a conversation mixes topics, let the assistant show a selectable context table before generating nodes or review cards.</item>
        <item>Keep large source material in Nodes/Capture slips instead of pasting everything into chat; local search sends only short excerpts.</item>
    </string-array>
    <string-array name="assistant_guide_safety">
        <item>The model never directly creates, renames, moves, or deletes Areas or Nodes in the database.</item>
        <item>Draft, capture-save, and review-save actions require an explicit app action; local search is read-only.</item>
        <item>Unknown Area names are not accepted as real Areas. If needed, choose or create the Area yourself before saving.</item>
        <item>Existing object edits carry revision checks, so stale drafts do not overwrite changed local content silently.</item>
    </string-array>
    <string-array name="assistant_guide_rollback">
        <item>If a draft is wrong, discard it by leaving the editor without saving, or ask the assistant to regenerate.</item>
        <item>If a saved Node is wrong, edit it manually or move it to Trash; Trash can restore the Node before permanent deletion.</item>
        <item>Before larger cleanup or restore operations, export a backup from More -> Data.</item>
        <item>If AI settings fail, use Validate and Models under More -> Service before sending more assistant requests.</item>
    </string-array>

